-- Gazit to Invest $110 Million in Indian Property Fund
-- Tal Barak
-- 2007-08-26T15:33:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2007-08-26/gazit-to-invest-110-million-in-indian-property-fund-update1-.html

          
          
             Gazit-Globe Ltd. (GLOB) , an Israeli
developer of commercial property in  Canada , Europe and the U.S.,
said a unit agreed to invest about $110 million in Hiref
International LLC, an Indian real-estate fund.  
 The fund, which received investment commitments of $750
million from international groups, was founded by HDFC Group, the
Tel Aviv, Israel-based company said in an e-mailed statement
today. The fund will invest in different property developments in
India, including commercial centers. The unit wasn't identified
in the statement.  
 ``We are happy to announce our first operations in India, a
challenging country with a lot of potential,'' said Gazit-Globe
Chief Executive Officer Haim Kaztman. ``We believe that doing the
first investment through the international fund will allow for a
gradual and careful way in.''  
 Gazit-Globe shares climbed 1.87 shekels, or 4 percent, to
49.25 in  Tel Aviv , the highest in a month.  
